  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes arguments for instantiating or cloning a typeface with specific variation and palette settings.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct that bundles the parameters used when creating or cloning a typeface with a particular variation design position, collection index, palette selection, and palette color overrides. Pass it to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)> to produce a new typeface instance with the requested settings.

Because this is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 0,
};
using var cloned = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
